http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Sankranti-windfall-for-RTC-Kurnool-region/article14009654.ece

The Andhra Pradesh State Road Transport Corporation (APSRTC), Kurnool region has generated a revenue of Rs. 1.58 crore during the Sankranti season by plying special bus services from this district to various parts of the State, RTC Regional Manager G. Venkateswara Rao said on Tuesday.One hundred special buses were plied during the festive season, he told the media here.Giving details about the financial health of the Corporation in this region, he said that the loss was reduced to Rs. 44 crore between April and December last year, when compared to the Rs. 63 crore in the corresponding period the previous year.